article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 79, Wofford 54
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 25 points as College of Charleston swept its season series with Wofford, romping to a 79-54 victory Thursday night in their second meeting. Though Wofford led 34-32 at halftime, the Cougars (16-7, 9-2 Southern Conference) took charge with a 20-4 run early in the second half. Antwaine Wiggins' jumper with 7:43 left ended the spurt and the Cougars led 60-42. Wiggins had 13 points and Willis Hall added 10 for Charleston, which moved a half-game ahead of the Terriers (12-11, 9-3) in the conference's South Division standings. Wofford trailed by as many as 28 points during a second half in which it was outscored 47-20. Noah Dahlman had 22 points to lead the Terriers, but he was their only player in double figures. Goudelock made four 3-pointers on a night in which Charleston made 10 of 26 from beyond the arc, while Wofford was only 2 of 8.
